# AGENTS

Guidance for AI coding agents working on the `tauri-kits` codebase.
This document describes the project layout, conventions, and the
end-to-end workflow for adding a new business module.

---

## 1. Project Overview

`tauri-kits` is a Tauri 2 desktop starter kit:

- Frontend: React 19 + TypeScript + Vite 7 + Ant Design 6
- State / Routing: React Router 7, lightweight React Context store
- i18n: i18next (`src/lang/en.ts`, `src/lang/zh.ts`)
- Backend: Rust in `src-tauri/`, SQLite via `sqlx`
- IPC: `@tauri-apps/api/core` `invoke()` calling `#[tauri::command]` functions

Reference module: `user` (page, form, API file, Rust commands, DB init).

---

## 2. Conventions

### Naming

- Frontend module directory: `src/components/<module>/` (all module files inside,
  including the page component as `index.tsx`).
- Frontend API file: `src/api/<module>.ts` (lowercase, one file per module).
- Frontend store file: `src/store/<module>.ts` (one file per module).
- Rust module file: `src-tauri/src/api/<module>.rs` (one file per module,
  never append new commands to `api.rs`).
- Rust commands: `api_<module>_<action>` (snake_case), e.g. `api_product_list`.
- Database table: singular snake_case, e.g. `user`, `product_category`.
- Route path: `/<module>` (kebab-case), e.g. `/user`, `/order-item`.
- i18n keys: grouped by feature, see `src/lang/en.ts` and `src/lang/zh.ts`.

### IPC response shape

Every Rust command returns:

```rust
pub struct ApiResponse<T> {
    pub code: i32,        // 200 = success
    pub message: String,
    pub data: Option<T>,
}
```

The frontend wraps `invoke()` and throws on non-200 codes (see
[src/api/user.ts](file:///e:/ruixinglong/tauri-kits/src/api/user.ts)).

### Styling

- One SCSS file per page: `<Module>.scss` co-located with the page component.
- Use the existing class layout: `.page-header`, `.stats-row`, `.search-card`,
  `.table-card` for visual consistency.

### i18n

- All user-visible strings must go through `t('...')` from `react-i18next`.
- Add keys to BOTH `src/lang/en.ts` and `src/lang/zh.ts`.

