## 4. Common Pitfalls

- **Appending new commands to `api.rs`** — every new module MUST live in its
  own file `src-tauri/src/api/<module>.rs`. Keep only shared types
  (`ApiResponse`, `PageResponse`) and the `get_db_pool` helper in `api.rs`.
- **Putting module components in `src/components/` root** — module pages MUST
  live in their own directory `src/components/<module>/`. Never create
  `<Module>.tsx` directly under `src/components/`.
- **Putting module state in `src/store/index.tsx`** — module-specific state
  MUST live in `src/store/<module>.ts`. The global `index.tsx` should only
  contain app-wide concerns like authentication.
- **Putting module `invoke()` calls in shared files** — module business APIs
  MUST live in `src/api/<module>.ts`. Never add `api_<module>_*` invokes to
  `src/api/request.ts` or `src/api/db.ts`; those are for cross-module
  helpers only.
- **Forgetting to register the command** in `lib.rs` — `invoke` will throw
  "command not found". Use the fully-qualified path
  `api::<module>::api_<module>_<action>`.
- **Inlining DDL in `api_db_init`** — each module owns its
  `api_<module>_init` command; `api_db_init` only delegates.
- **Mismatched invoke argument names** — Rust `page_size` must be called with
  `pageSize` from JS for primitives; struct args keep their original name.
- **Returning password hashes** — always blank out sensitive fields before
  sending the struct back to the frontend.
- **i18n keys only in one language** — every key must exist in both
  `en.ts` and `zh.ts`, otherwise the UI shows the raw key.
- **Skipping the SCSS file** — pages without scoped styles break the
  `.page-wrapper` card layout.

