## 5. CHANGELOG Standards

All notable changes must be documented in `CHANGELOG.md`. Follow the
[keepachangelog.com](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.0.0/) format:

```markdown
## [version] - YYYY-MM-DD

### Added

- **Feature Name** - Description of the new feature
  - Sub-item details

### Changed

- **Change Name** - Description of the change
  - Sub-item details

### Fixed

- **Bug Name** - Description of the bug fix
  - Sub-item details

---
```

Rules:

- Each version gets its own section with release date (YYYY-MM-DD).
- Use the three standard categories: `Added`, `Changed`, `Fixed`.
- Group related changes under a feature/change/bug name with a bold header.
- Include sub-item details using nested bullet points when needed.
- Always link to the relevant issue or PR if applicable.
- Keep entries concise but descriptive enough for readers to understand
  what changed without reading code.

